article.headline: Redhawks rush for season-high in 38-23 victory
article.description: Alonzo Smith ran for 164 of the RedHawks' season-high 289 yards rushing and Miami (Ohio) defeated Bowling Green 38-23 in a Mid-America Conference opener on Saturday.
article.linkText: Redhawks rush for season-high in 38-23 victory

images.name: Thomas scampers in for 30-yard  TD
images.caption: Maurice Thomas turns the corner and runs for a 30-yard Miami (OH) touchdown.

video.headline: Thomas scampers in for 30-yard  TD
video.caption: Maurice Thomas turns the corner and runs for a 30-yard Miami (OH) touchdown.
video.title: Thomas scampers in for 30-yard  TD
video.description: Maurice Thomas turns the corner and runs for a 30-yard Miami (OH) touchdown.

article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- Alonzo Smith ran for 164 of the RedHawks' season-high 289 yards rushing and Miami (Ohio) defeated Bowling Green 38-23 in a Mid-America Conference opener on Saturday. Smith's 34-yard run put the senior over 2,000 yards rushing for his career and set Miami (1-3, 1-0) up at the Falcons 2-yard line before Gus Ragland ran over from the 1 two plays later for a 17-3 lead. Ragland tossed a 6-yard pass to Andrew Homer with 33 seconds left in the first half to go up 24-3. The lead grew to 31-3 on Ragland's 26-yard pass to Jack Sorenson in the third quarter before the Falcons (1-3, 0-1) scored their remaining points in the final 5 1/2 minutes of the game. Ragland was an efficient 10-of-15 passing for 119 yards and two scores. Bowling Green's Jarret Doege threw 45 times, completing 30, for 237 yards and two scores. Grant Loy added a TD pass on the game's final play.

videos.headline: Bowling Green' Sawmiller catches a tip-drill TD to end game
videos.description: Grant Loy throws up a prayer that is caught off the tip by Justin Sawmiller for a 40-yard touchdown to end Bowling Green's loss to Miami (OH).
